snippet.textDisplay: My husband and I watched (binged) about 4 episodes the other night (for the first time) we both cried 😭 you two were our favorite couple and oh man! My first husband and I were interracial .. I’m a mix of Latin-Native American and he was White/Black but since he was darker skinned he felt all of the things one would deal with as a black man- especially because his father left and his white side raised him and he felt outcasted. Ironically he was always insecure I would leave him for a white guy 🤷🏻‍♀️ although I assured him I was happy- he allowed his insecurities to rule his heart and after 7yrs of marriage- 3 kids later... he cheated and left us. That was in 2001. I remarried in 2014 and have 2 more children. But I get your relationship and everything that plays a role in it. The three children we had together are now 19, 24, & 25 they are so talented and beautiful (not just saying it because I’m their mother;) they get so much attention for their good looks, humor, talent and kindness ♥️ Never - Ever allow race to rule the relationship- it’s love pure unconditional love that rules it. The children you will have together will be the gift! We are all created by God and nothing else matters in the end!
